# API Design

## REST API Standards (Hono-based)
- Use consistent URL patterns and HTTP methods
- Implement proper status codes and error responses
- Add request/response validation
- Include pagination for list endpoints
- Provide comprehensive API documentation

## MCP Protocol Standards
- Follow MCP specification exactly
- Implement proper tool schemas with validation
- Use streaming for large data sets
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Include proper resource management

## Hono Route Structure
```typescript
import { Hono } from 'hono'
import { cors } from 'hono/cors'
import { logger } from 'hono/logger'

const app = new Hono()

// Middleware
app.use('*', cors())
app.use('*', logger())

// Routes
app.route('/api/v1', apiRoutes)
app.route('/mcp', mcpRoutes)
app.route('/ws', websocketRoutes)
```
